<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1954-12-31T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1951-09-27T10:00:00-05:00" n="1323" subtype="editorial-note" type="document" xml:id="d1323">
                            <head>No. 1323<lb/><hi rend="italic">Editorial Note</hi></head>
                            <p>On April 17, 1954, General <persName corresp="#p_NGM1">Muhammad
                                        <persName corresp="#p_NGM1">Naguib</persName>
                                </persName> resigned as Prime Minister of Egypt and was replaced by
                                Colonel <persName corresp="#p_NCGA1">Gamal Abdul Nasir</persName>,
                                who retained his chairmanship of the Revolutionary Command Council.
                                General <persName corresp="#p_NGM1">Naguib</persName> remained
                                President of Egypt until November 15, 1954.</p>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>